Is the lag acceptable now ? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=whistlerfv>Whistler FV</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#A62A2A>(11/20/03 8:21 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2128.topic&index=3>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: .</span><hr size=1> &quot;How about an update Whistler? &quot;<br>
<br>
You got it.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
&quot;You know.... sadly, many people never gave SB a chance because it has outdated graphics to begin with. &quot;<br>
<br>
The graphics will be improved some with Rise of Chaos, however they still don't come close to what is widely considered the best graphics around: DAOC. That being said, I don't play this game for the graphics; I play because it's PvP &amp; Nation building, two things I'm quite fond of.<br>
<br>
Oh, and the Dungeon Siege clicky thing is still how you get around. That was really annoying at first but I got used to it fairly quickly. Some people prefer it, and some will never like it.<br>
<br>
&quot;What content was added? &quot;<br>
<br>
Expansion has new race, couple new classes, but there are still NO quests you can do. One cool thing about the game is that if you want to set up your own Merchant city, you can easily do so. Construct your buildings, walls, towers, etc, get your merchants set up, and start cranking out specific classes of items for other PC's to buy.<br>
<br>
Also, there is not a lot of item variation. There are basically 3 classes of item for each type. For example, movement speed boots, if they end in &quot;of Winds&quot;, it's +5% movement bonus, &quot;of the Zephyr&quot; is +10%, and &quot;of Windlords&quot; is +15%. All items will effect your stats, abilities, skills, defense values, etc. But there isn't nearly the variation that EQ has. EQ has more variation than any other mmorpg. SB is definitely not an item based game.<br>
<br>
It really is a PvP, nation building, siege warfare game and not much else. Although, there is some nice RP that goes on sometimes. It's much easier to RP when you can PvP imho.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Oh, and they do have a fair amount of Lore in the game, and one of the servers has special Lore rules that are conducive to RP (for example xp bonus for certain classes/races depending on guild type), so it's very easy to set up an RP guild if you want.<br>
<br>
<br>
&quot;And finally.... how is the PvP war aspect of the game coming along? Do you FEEL like you actually belong to some player-created nation/empire? Does the PvP warfare flow smoothly? Are there regular sieges of player cities? &quot;<br>
<br>
Very nicely. Yes, yes (now), and yes, depending on what server you're on.<br>
 <br>
&quot;Did it stop crashing ?&quot;<br>
<br>
Yes. Crashes are rare now.<br>
<br>
&quot;Is the lag acceptable now ?&quot;<br>
<br>
Yes, and they fixed it faster than EQ did after it's release.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
You still need a decent system to play, though, and it's still best to minimize video settings in mass siege situations when you have 40 v 40, etc.<br>
